The paper focuses on studying the relationship between human attention and language constructs during image captioning tasks, as well as analyzing attention deployment mechanisms in the top-down soft attention approach. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks and machine learning techniques, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper also touches on human-computer interaction and cognitive psychology, suggesting that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
